The React [docs](https://reactjs.org/docs/react-component.html#componentdidmount) don't suggest calling `this.setState` in `componentDidMount` for performance reasons. We can avoid this by having this logic in the constructor.

```jsx
constructor(props) {
  super(props);
  
  // ...
  
  this.state = {
    // ...
  };
}
```

_Note: We might not be able to call `this.<something>` inside the constructor so we would need to extract things like `getScopesetDiff` and  `getCellColors` to be outside the class. Putting them after the imports lines of this file sounds good to me._

